==English==

===Etymology===
From the standard accounting practice of using red ink to denote negative values, especially a [[net loss]].

===Adjective===
'''[[in]] [[the]] [[red]]'''
#[[Category:English idioms]] {{accounting}} Having [[net loss]]es.
#:''The figures are going to be '''in the red''' this year.''

====Antonym====
*[[in the black]]

